to the editor you correctly applaud president clinton 's call for 1 billion to help hire more health care workers editorial sept 25 the skilled nursing community is experiencing the most challenging labor market in memory several weeks ago the american health care association called upon congress and the clinton administration to join us in an effort to attract more than 250000 new certified nursing assistants into the profession by 2002 we agree with you that if congress does indeed try to mandate staffing ratios it must also be ready to step up to its financing obligations we believe that staffing mandates must be fully financed all parties agree on the need to increase staffing levels in america 's nursing homes we look forward to working with the president and congress to make this goal a reality charles h roadman ii md president and chief executive american health care association washington sept 28 2000

